Simpson & Partners is one of those brands that divides the EV charging market into two camps: people who haven't heard of them, and people who are evangelical about them. This small, Cotswolds-based manufacturer has quietly built a reputation for producing some of the most beautifully crafted home EV chargers in the UK — earning an Auto Express Best Buy award and a loyal following among design-conscious EV owners.

The Home Series V3 is their latest wall-mount charger, and on paper it's compelling: premium anodised aluminium construction, up to 132 colour combinations, an industry-leading 10-year warranty, and compatibility with Intelligent Octopus Go. But at a price point above many mainstream rivals, is the premium justified?

