## Our Verdict

**Rating: ★★★★☆ 4.4/5**

The Simpson & Partners Home Series V3 is a charger you buy with your heart as much as your head. The build quality is genuinely in a league of its own — nothing else in this market feels this premium, looks this elegant, or offers this level of customisation. The 10-year warranty backs that up with a guarantee no competitor can match.

The addition of Intelligent Octopus Go and OVO Charge Anytime integration addresses what was previously the charger's biggest weakness, bringing it into line with smarter rivals. Solar compatibility on the Plus model rounds out a strong feature set.

But the app lets it down. At this price point, software should be as polished as the hardware, and it isn't. The lack of standard 4G connectivity is a penny-pinching move that doesn't suit a premium product. And the price climbs steeply once you start ticking option boxes.

**Buy the Simpson & Partners if:** Design and build quality are your top priorities. You want a charger that looks like a piece of architectural hardware, not a utility box. The 10-year warranty matters to you. You appreciate UK craftsmanship and customisation options.

**Look elsewhere if:** You want the best app experience — the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) or [Hypervolt Home 3 Pro](/reviews/hypervolt-home-3-review/) are both stronger on software. If budget is a concern, the [Pod Point Solo 3](/reviews/pod-point-solo-3-review/) or Ohme deliver more value for less money.

