## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is the Simpson & Partners charger compatible with Intelligent Octopus Go?

Yes. The Home Series V3 is fully compatible with Intelligent Octopus Go, allowing automatic scheduling of charging during the cheapest overnight slots. It's also compatible with OVO Charge Anytime. This is a relatively recent addition — earlier Simpson & Partners models didn't support smart tariffs.

### What does the 10-year warranty cover?

The 10-year warranty covers the charger enclosure — the physical housing and external components. It's the longest warranty in the UK home EV charger market. Internal electronics are covered under a separate standard warranty period. Contact Simpson & Partners directly for full warranty terms.

### Can I change the colour of my Simpson & Partners charger later?

The colour is chosen at the point of order and is part of the physical construction (anodised aluminium). However, the lid (metal or wood) can potentially be swapped. If you're unsure about colour, the Basic model offers four safe choices, while the Plus opens up 132 combinations.

### Does the Simpson & Partners charger have a display?

No. The Home Series V3 doesn't have an LCD display — all management is done through the smartphone app. Some competing chargers, like the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/), include a small display for at-a-glance status information.

### Is Simpson & Partners a reliable brand?

Simpson & Partners is a smaller, specialist manufacturer based in the Cotswolds, founded in 2018. They have a 4.3-star rating on Trustpilot and their charger won an Auto Express Best Buy award. They're trusted by over 700 qualified electricians in the UK. While they don't have the scale of Ohme or myenergi, their focus on quality and repairability sets them apart.

